1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 18=

3
00:01:47,790 --> 00:01:48,550
You're still awake?

4
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:50,490
I thought you had forgotten
the way home.

5
00:01:55,910 --> 00:01:56,840
I got you some congee.

6
00:01:57,250 --> 00:01:58,410
It's good for your stomach.

7
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,790
Come and have some.

8
00:02:41,510 --> 00:02:42,630
Have some pickled vegetables.

9
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:52,350
Your dad's getting old.

10
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,950
It's normal for him

11
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,110
to overlook things.

12
00:02:56,790 --> 00:02:58,670
Let's not fight over this, okay?

13
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,910
We should stick together

14
00:03:00,910 --> 00:03:02,630
and talk to him as a team.

15
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,830
Did you see his attitude today?

16
00:03:06,230 --> 00:03:07,750
How are we supposed to reason with him?

17
00:03:09,830 --> 00:03:10,440
Then

18
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,440
we'll do it your way.

19
00:03:13,350 --> 00:03:15,160
Your dad visits Ms. Nie

20
00:03:15,830 --> 00:03:17,000
at the nursing home every day.

21
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:19,100
You drop him off and I'll pick him up.

22
00:03:20,110 --> 00:03:20,990
You're okay with that?

23
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,870
There's a Jacky Cheung concert
on Friday.

24
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:25,580
If you're willing to go with me,
I'll do it.

25
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,040
Friday?

26
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:32,630
I've got an industry conference.

27
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,470
It's going to be all day.

28
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,620
- Even in the evening?
- Yes, even in the evening.

29
00:03:39,670 --> 00:03:40,910
We had a deal.

30
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:42,300
So, no backing out.

31
00:03:42,670 --> 00:03:44,760
I'm not backing out. Didn't we agree

32
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,320
to make a plan and take it slow?

33
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:50,600
Who knows what will happen tomorrow?

34
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:51,830
Just look at Ms. Nie.

35
00:03:51,830 --> 00:03:53,350
There's no time to waste.

36
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,950
Lina, I really don't have time.

37
00:04:00,630 --> 00:04:01,830
You've got time to run

38
00:04:01,830 --> 00:04:02,880
and time to drink.

39
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,070
But no time for your wife?

40
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:05,760
Where does all your time go?

41
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:08,880
Ms. Nie has a terminal illness,

42
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:10,210
and your dad still sticks by her.

43
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,440
I'm still in my prime.

44
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:13,880
But you won't even look at me
when you come home.

45
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:16,280
It's not like I'm slacking off.
I'm just busy.

46
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,160
Look.

47
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:20,440
look at all these meeting alerts.

48
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,680
See? Just look.

49
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,750
- Look.
- I don't want to look at it.

50
00:04:28,470 --> 00:04:29,240
I'll do it.

51
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,020
- Let me do it.
- Be careful. It's hot.

52
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,590
I didn't mean it.

53
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:38,320
Can

54
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,050
you still switch it on?

55
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,810
Give me your phone.

56
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,270
What's Jin's phone number?

57
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,470
I have Jin's number.

58
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,440
You have it?

59
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:29,880
Jin,

60
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:31,760
- Yes, Mr. Shen.
- Tell Dong Gong

61
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,470
to call this number right away.

62
00:05:33,470 --> 00:05:34,320
It's urgent.

63
00:05:34,950 --> 00:05:36,270
Okay, I'll let him know.

64
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:46,590
Try again.

65
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,030
Dong Gong?

66
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,240
I need to ask you a tech question.

67
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:55,930
What is it?

68
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,560
I dropped my phone in the congee.
Can the data still be recovered?

69
00:05:58,800 --> 00:05:59,860
Isn't there a cloud backup?

70
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:03,240
Normally, there's a backup in the cloud.

71
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,810
You see, we're reviewing a contract with the client,

72
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,360
and we signed an NDA.

73
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,630
All the related data can't be uploaded

74
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,200
to the cloud.

75
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,280
I usually back it up
to my computer every day.

76
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:15,519
But I've been swamped
and skipped the last couple of days.

77
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:17,400
And we collected a lot of data
during that time.

78
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:18,390
Then it's hard to say.

79
00:06:19,390 --> 00:06:20,910
We'll have to check tomorrow morning.

80
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:23,150
Can you come in early tomorrow?

81
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,500
Okay, I'll be there early.

82
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:25,880
So, can it be recovered?

83
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,810
I don't know!

84
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:34,320
So, can the message

85
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,720
I sent you earlier still be found?

86
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:37,950
That's what you care about right now?

87
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,710
What's your problem?

88
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,559
You come home
and drop your phone in the congee.

89
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,950
Are you hiding something from me

90
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:44,680
on your phone?

91
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,730
Did you do it on purpose?

92
00:06:47,030 --> 00:06:48,760
Yes! I did it on purpose!

93
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,360
I have secrets on my phone!

94
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,030
My phone is full of secrets!

95
00:06:52,150 --> 00:06:53,830
I wanted to destroy the evidence, okay?

96
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,270
If you leave, don't ever come back!

97
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:49,000
Mr. Shen?

98
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:51,830
Mr. Shen.

99
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:53,760
Why are you here?

100
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,810
Why didn't you go home?

101
00:07:56,030 --> 00:07:57,000
I came

102
00:07:57,830 --> 00:07:58,560
to find a report.

103
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,760
And what are you doing here?

104
00:08:01,510 --> 00:08:02,680
After you and Ice left,

105
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,879
we just sat around in silence.

106
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,510
It was sort of pointless
so everyone left.

107
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,100
I came back to grab something.

108
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,440
Okay.

109
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,630
Go ahead.

110
00:09:16,352 --> 00:09:19,470
(Male: Shen Qing. Female: Liu Lina.
Together forever.)

111
00:09:42,690 --> 00:09:47,840
(Ms. Nie's medication schedule. Monday.
Valsartan. Morning. Noon. Evening. Felodipine. Evening)

112
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,710
Ms. Nie, do you know

113
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:57,350
Professor Shen

114
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,590
got into a fight with his kids

115
00:10:01,070 --> 00:10:02,830
just to find you a good nursing home.

116
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,560
We're both women.

117
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,110
I've lived over half my life.

118
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:19,280
But no one ever cared
about me like that.

119
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:33,830
Ms. Nie,

120
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:37,830
you're really lucky.

121
00:11:08,230 --> 00:11:08,870
Dong Gong, so?

122
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:10,590
Can you fix it?

123
00:11:11,990 --> 00:11:12,870
It's hard to tell.

124
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,280
I can only try.

125
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,520
I don't care about the phone.

126
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,520
I only care if the data
can be recovered.

127
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,210
How about this?

128
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,280
I'll take a look at it
after I take it apart.

129
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:24,919
I'll get you a backup phone.

130
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:25,520
Okay.

131
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:27,439
I'm counting on you.

132
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,040
Wait here.

133
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:39,750
Ms. Nie.

134
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:40,640
Yulan.

135
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:41,870
I am here to see you.

136
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:44,309
Thank goodness you're here.

137
00:11:44,310 --> 00:11:45,940
Please try to talk some sense
into Ms. Nie.

138
00:11:45,990 --> 00:11:48,070
She insists on going downstairs
to the garden.

139
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,230
With her health condition, is it safe?

140
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,680
You want to go to the garden?

141
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:56,590
I made a promise to Professor Shen.

142
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:06,300
How about this?

143
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:08,710
I'll take Ms. Nie to the garden.

144
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:10,870
Okay.

145
00:12:10,990 --> 00:12:11,950
Let's go.

146
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:14,230
Ms. Nie,

147
00:12:14,990 --> 00:12:16,540
do you want to put on a little lipstick?

148
00:12:16,710 --> 00:12:18,110
It'll brighten up your complexion.

149
00:12:20,470 --> 00:12:21,280
Okay.

150
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:22,160
Here.

151
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,600
I'll help you put it on.

152
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,800
I've got one right here.

153
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,830
If anything happens, it's on you.

154
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,800
Of course.

155
00:12:42,710 --> 00:12:43,870
Take a look. Is it pretty?

156
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:51,440
Beautiful.

157
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:53,520
You look pretty.

158
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,470
It smells so nice.

159
00:13:03,710 --> 00:13:04,260
It sure does.

160
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:06,870
Easy now.

161
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:07,830
Gently.

162
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:11,300
It smells lovely.

163
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:14,350
Yulan,

164
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,590
I don't know how to thank you.

165
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:19,640
Oh, don't be silly.

166
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:21,750
This pen

167
00:13:22,590 --> 00:13:23,680
is my favorite.

168
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,440
I'll give it to you
as a little keepsake.

169
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,470
It's so beautiful.

170
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,520
Thank you so much.

171
00:13:34,990 --> 00:13:35,840
I'll accept it then.

172
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:39,230
Then I'll use this pen to learn from you

173
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,680
and practice my writing.

174
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:41,750
You're too kind.

175
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,870
Professor Shen is here.

176
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:53,040
Ms. Nie.

177
00:13:58,990 --> 00:14:00,470
you look much better.

178
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:02,040
Really?

179
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:02,800
Of course.

180
00:14:02,990 --> 00:14:03,950
Please, have a seat.

181
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:06,070
You too.

182
00:14:06,230 --> 00:14:07,070
What did I tell you?

183
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,450
With how advanced medicine is

184
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:11,040
these days,

185
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,560
we'll definitely beat this illness.

186
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:15,740
Oh right,

187
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:16,870
look at this.

188
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,680
I recorded

189
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:19,870
our rehearsal.

190
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:23,040
Watch it.

191
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:28,440
♪What a beautiful jasmine flower♪

192
00:14:28,950 --> 00:14:36,800
♪No flower in the whole garden
smells as sweet♪

193
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:38,040
Everyone sings very well.

194
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:39,200
Not bad, right?

195
00:14:39,280 --> 00:14:41,470
♪I want to pick one and wear it♪

196
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,350
I was thinking

197
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:03,590
we could swap out that Kunqu lyric

198
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:06,320
for a better line.

199
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:09,230
Let me think.

200
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:11,160
No rush so take your time.

201
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:15,280
You missed the last rehearsal.

202
00:15:16,110 --> 00:15:16,710
But it's okay.

203
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,440
We'll go together

204
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:20,410
for the real performance.

205
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:22,710
Gou will definitely

206
00:15:22,710 --> 00:15:24,200
thank our literary advisor,

207
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,280
Ms. Nie Juanjuan,

208
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:27,800
during the opening speech.

209
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,200
Speaking of Gou,

210
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:35,940
here is Gou's wedding confection.

211
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:37,780
A bit of good luck.

212
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:39,470
Gou is married?

213
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,070
Yes.

214
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:41,920
He had a wedding reception.

215
00:15:43,870 --> 00:15:44,680
It was lovely.

216
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,350
At the ceremony,

217
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,790
he got really emotional and said,

218
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:50,690
"Tianzhen and I met halfway

219
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:52,680
through life,

220
00:15:53,830 --> 00:15:54,950
and now we'll walk

221
00:15:55,830 --> 00:15:56,750
the second half

222
00:15:57,710 --> 00:15:58,280
together."

223
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,470
That line

224
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:09,640
really moved me.

225
00:16:14,110 --> 00:16:14,590
Ms. Nie,

226
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,380
I want to say the same to you.

227
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,350
Let's walk

228
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,480
the second half of life together.

229
00:16:43,710 --> 00:16:44,200
Ah,

230
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:45,700
there's one more thing

231
00:16:46,990 --> 00:16:47,920
to tell you.

232
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,400
My life plan.

233
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:51,920
This

234
00:16:52,990 --> 00:16:53,520
and this too.

235
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:55,870
My daughter found

236
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,870
many rehabilitation nursing homes

237
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,230
for me online

238
00:16:59,230 --> 00:17:01,950
and through various channels.

239
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:05,470
I've checked out several in person.

240
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,440
You wouldn't believe
how nice the places were.

241
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:09,880
I am really impressed.

242
00:17:10,470 --> 00:17:11,220
So I was thinking,

243
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:12,790
once you're discharged,

244
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,310
we could move there together.

245
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:21,200
If you think

246
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:23,650
these two are too far

247
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:24,920
from home.

248
00:17:25,550 --> 00:17:26,310
There are others.

249
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:27,400
Here,

250
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:28,880
these are good too.

251
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:32,310
And these.

252
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,380
Take a look at these.

253
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:36,260
Look at this one.

254
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:10,549
It was you who suggested to Dad

255
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:12,220
about moving into a nursing home,
wasn't it?

256
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:14,880
Can you stop causing trouble back here
while you're overseas?

257
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:16,470
I'm not causing trouble.

258
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:18,680
I may live abroad.

259
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:19,550
But

260
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,790
I am still a Chinese.

261
00:18:22,790 --> 00:18:23,510
Besides,

262
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,080
you should try to understand Dad.

263
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,200
Mr. Shen.

264
00:18:28,860 --> 00:18:29,839
Whatever, I'm busy now.

265
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:30,700
I have to hang up now.

266
00:18:32,550 --> 00:18:33,269
How did it go?

267
00:18:33,270 --> 00:18:34,370
I managed to fix the phone.

268
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,030
But

269
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:36,470
the data can't be recovered.

270
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,700
Remember to back up
your data regularly from now on.

271
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,360
Okay, I will.

272
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,440
So

273
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:43,920
after I swap out the SIM card,

274
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,680
I'll have Jin return your phone.

275
00:18:45,950 --> 00:18:46,270
Okay.

276
00:18:58,880 --> 00:18:59,310
Come in.

277
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:00,880
Ice.

278
00:19:01,950 --> 00:19:02,510
You're here.

279
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:03,270
I'm sorry.

280
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:04,200
It's okay.

281
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:07,180
We'll redo everything quickly
so we can still pass tomorrow's review.

282
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,270
Have a seat.
I'll send you the contract file.

283
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,950
We'll each fill in our part.

284
00:19:12,710 --> 00:19:13,810
Thank you for helping out.

285
00:19:18,177 --> 00:19:19,710
(ICE Investment Terms List)

286
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:21,880
I got it.

287
00:19:52,470 --> 00:19:53,550
